exophoric pragmatic iconicity, a language-external iconic relationship based on similarity between linguistic structure and the speaker/writer's conceptualization of reality, and endophoric iconicity, a language-internal iconic relationship where the iconic ground is construed between linguistic signs and structures. Analogy is viewed as a productive process that generalizes patterns or extends grammatical rules to formally similar structures, and obtains the form of the analogical relationship between the masculine singular definite article and the third person singular accusative clitic, which shared the same phonotactically constrained distribution patterns. The data indicate that exophoric pragamatic iconicity exploits and maintains the alternation, whereas endophoric iconicity and analogy conspire to end it.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aIconicity (Linguistics) 0aIconicity (Linguistics). 0aItalian languagexClitics. 0aItalian languagexDialectsxGrammarxItalyxTuscany. 0aItalian languagexDialectsxGrammar, HistoricalxItalyxTuscany. 0aItalian languagexDialectszItalyzTuscanyxGrammar, Historical. 0aItalian languagexDialectszItalyzTuscanyxGrammar. 0aItalian languagexGrammar, Historical. 0aItalian languagexPronoun. 0aLinguistic changexItalyxTuscany. 0aLinguistic change. 4aAnalogy. 4aClitic Pronouns. 4aIconicity. 4aItalienisch. 4aPragmatic Functionality. 4aSprachwandel. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aRussi, Cinzia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguis